  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Children with acute diseases with oral ulcers (not included PRESENTATIONS OF SLE, IBD or
      IMMUNOCOMPRMIZED STATES)will receive several doses (drinking or mouth rinsing) of either
      pasteurized goat milk or cow milk. Children will than be followed for length of the disease -
      signs and symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A prospective randomized controlled study that will include 110 previously health 6months - 5
      years children (55 in each group) with acute oral ulcer disease (&lt; 48 hours). Children will
      receive several doses (drinking or mouth rinsing) of either pasteurized goat milk or cow
      milk. Children will than be followed for length of the disease - sings and symptoms by
      questioner to parents, and physical examination by there physicians. .
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
